  "title": "Human Resource Executive (Temp)",
  "description": "<p>Responsible for the managing HR administration responsibilities and supporting the full spectrum of HR functions such as recruitment, onboarding, administration, compensation and benefits, training and employee relations</p><p><strong>Duties and Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li><p>Manage employee benefit administration</p></li><li><p>Ensure timely and accurate submission of employee details</p></li><li><p>Screen resumes and communicate to line managers on potential candidates</p></li><li><p>Arrange interviews & reference checks</p></li><li><p>Manage all HR administration such as personnel files, contracts, letters, uniform fitting, lockers, application, renewal and cancellation of work passes</p></li><li><p>Work with department heads on employees’ probationary assessments and confirmation</p></li><li><p>Prepare letters for promotions, transfers, acceptance of resignation & employment certificates</p></li><li><p>Assist with employee relations issues in a confidential manner, including disciplinary and employee grievances.</p></li><li><p>Prepare month end reports such as Annual Leave balance, Headcount, Turnover</p></li><li><p>Assist to drive welfare and recreation activities for the colleagues including but not limited to Employee Touch Points</p></li><li><p>Assist to co-organize Staff Events</p></li><li><p>Manage part-time and casual labour recruitment, administration and onboarding</p></li><li><p>Support the administration of the Employee Recognition program</p></li><li><p>Supports and ensures 100% compliance in Brand Standards, Finance & HR Audits</p></li><li><p>Maintain records of training attendance</p></li></ul>",
